                <note rend="inline" type="source">821.7961/5: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-02-15T12:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 15, 1929—noon</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>14. The Department is very anxious about the aviation agreement with Colombia.
                    Has any progress been made with the agreement and do you think it can be
                    concluded shortly? In view of the conditions presented in Department’s 11,
                    February 9, noon, time is of the essence in the matter.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
